<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Jorge Montt</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Iquique</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-05-16"><hi rend="italic">May 16,
                                1891</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>We have the honor to inform your excellency that Mr. Richard L. Trumbull,
                            a representative in the Chilean Congress, has powers from the
                            Governmental Junta to represent us in the United States in the capacity
                            of confidential agent.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased, your excellency, to accept him in that capacity.</p>
                        <closer><signed>
                                <list>
                                    <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Montt</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">President of the Governmental Junta</hi>.</item>
                                    <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Isidoro Errazuriz</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary Foreign Relations</hi>.</item>
                                </list>
                            </signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>